sentences: Born in Istanbul in 1944, she began her career at the Istanbul Municipal Conservatory.
In 1957, she was sent to study at the Conservatoire de Paris under Turkish law no. 6660 for students with "extraordinary talents."
She won first prize in the Marguerite Long-Jacques Thibaud Competition (now called the Long-Thibaud-Crespin Competition) in Paris in October 1963.
In 1965, Erman placed second in the Canada International Piano Competition.
Verda Erman was honored as a State Artist in 1971, the year the honorary title was created.
She toured extensively around the world as a guest musician after 1971.
Erman died in Paris on 21 July 2014, possibly of leukemia, at the age of 70.

sentences: Verda Erman (19 December 1944 – 21 July 2014) was a Turkish pianist.
She won first prize in the Marguerite Long-Jacques Thibaud Competition (now called the Long-Thibaud-Crespin Competition) in Paris in October 1963.
Verda Erman was honored as a State Artist in 1971, the year the honorary title was created.
